<p>My aim is for a user to be able to change the inputs to a linear regression model in a Shiny application, and for the Shiny application to show the forecast based on the value of the variables given.</p>  <p>ie. a Chicken shop uses the variable Temperature and Day of the week to predict sales. I want a user to be able to change these variables to see the different forecasts.</p>  <pre><code>calculateModel &lt;- function(data,input){   regCT &lt;- reactive({tslm(Total ~ Monday,data=data)})   nextCT &lt;- data.frame(Monday=input$Monday)   fCT &lt;- forecast(regCT,newdata=nextCT)   return(fCT) }  ui &lt;- dashboardPage(   dashboardHeader(title = "Chicken"),   dashboardBody(     fluidRow(       box(plotOutput("main_plot", height = "300px")),       box(sliderInput("Monday","Monday",0,1,1)       )     )   ) ) server &lt;- shinyServer(function(input, output) {  dataInput &lt;- reactive({  calculateModel(daily,input) })    output$main_plot &lt;- renderPlot({     input$Monday     plot(fCT)    })  }) shinyApp(ui,server) </code></pre>  <p>This is a very rough outline of what I assume the code would look like. Any help would be greatly appreciated.</p>